### Before reporting an issue

- [X] I have searched existing issues
- [X] I have reproduced the issue with the [latest nightly release](https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/releases/tag/nightly)

### Area

account/ui

### Describe the bug

Continuing the work in https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/22432 and the corresponding PR https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/pull/22451. The `inputOptionLabels` user profile option, which can be used to specify translatable fields for a select, is not respected in the Account UI.

### Version

22

### Expected behavior

With inputOptionLabels I should be able to provide translated labels for select options in the account ui.

### Actual behavior

The inputOptionLabels option is ignored by account ui.

### How to Reproduce?

1. Add a custom attribute in the user profile:
```json
{
      "name": "attr",
      "displayName": "${attr}",
      "selector": {
        "scopes": [
          "microprofile-jwt",
          "phone",
          "profile",
          "email",
          "web-origins",
          "roles",
          "offline_access",
          "role_list",
          "address",
          "acr"
        ]
      },
      "permissions": {
        "edit": [
          "user",
          "admin"
        ],
        "view": [
          "user",
          "admin"
        ]
      },
      "annotations": {
        "inputType": "select",
        "inputOptionLabels": {
          "option1": "${option1Label}",
          "option2": "${option2Label}",
        }
      },
      "validations": {
        "options": {
          "options": [
            "option1",
            "option2"
          ]
        }
      },
      "required": {
        "roles": [
          "user"
        ],
        "scopes": [
          "microprofile-jwt",
          "phone",
          "profile",
          "email",
          "web-origins",
          "roles",
          "offline_access",
          "role_list",
          "address",
          "acr"
        ]
      },
      "group": null
    },
```
2. Check the account console for a user
3. It says `option1` and `option2` instead of `option1Label` and `option2Label`

### Anything else?

The corresponding source file https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/blob/main/js/apps/account-ui/src/personal-info/components/SelectComponent.tsx#L53:
```tsx
<Select
  toggleId={attribute.name}
  onToggle={(b) => setOpen(b)}
  onSelect={(_, value) => {
    const option = value.toString();
    if (Array.isArray(field.value)) {
      if (field.value.includes(option)) {
        field.onChange(
          field.value.filter((item: string) => item !== option),
        );
      } else {
        field.onChange([...field.value, option]);
      }
    } else {
      field.onChange(option);
      setOpen(false);
    }
  }}
  selections={field.value ? field.value : t("choose")}
  variant={Array.isArray(field.value) ? "typeaheadmulti" : "single"}
  aria-label={t("selectOne")}
  isOpen={open}
>
  {options.map((option) => (
    <SelectOption
      selected={field.value === option}
      key={option}
      value={option}
    >
      {option}
    </SelectOption>
  ))}
</Select>
```
